Residents and the disaster management team on Saturday worked to rescue a 33-year-old man who was buried alive in a pit latrine he was digging at Kegogi Market in Kitutu Chache North Constituency, Kisii County.Mr Joseph Nyakundi was among two others who were hired to dig the pit latrine at a home. The walls caved in, burying him alive.DISASTERThe County Disaster Management Director Julius Tinega said they received the report at around midday after his colleagues raised the alarm.“When we got here we established that Mr Nyakundi had been in the collapsed toilet from 10.30 in the morning and residents were already making efforts to rescue him,” he said.   More follows. 
 